There is a Quentin C. D. Bovey mentioned in the Supplements to the <em>London Gazette</em>:

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/29497/supplements/2443/" rel="nofollow">3rd March 1916</a>, p. 2443: &quot;The Gordon Highlanders. Temporary Lieutenant Quentin C. D. Bovey to be temporary Captain. Dated 20th July, 1915.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/29902/supplements/565/" rel="nofollow">12 January 1917</a>, p. 565: &quot;War Office, 13th January, 1917. REGULAR FORCES. INFANTRY. [...] Gord. Highrs. Temp. Capt. Q. C. D. Bovey, from a Serv. Bn., to be temp. Capt. (attd.). 5 Jan. 1917, with seniority from 20 July 1915.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/30684/supplements/5814/" rel="nofollow"> 15 May 1918</a>, p. 5814: &quot;ESTABLISHMENTS. PHYSICAL AND BAYONET TRAINING. Temp. Capt. Q. C. D. Bovey, attd. Gord. Highrs., to be an Asst. Supt., and to be transfd. to Gen. List. 4th Mar. 1918.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/30778/supplements/7859/" rel="nofollow">2 July 1918</a>, p. 7859: &quot;War Office, 4th July 1918. REGULAR FORCES. COMMANDS AND STAFF. The undermentioned appts. are made: -- PERSONAL STAFF. A.D.C.--Temp. Capt. Q. C. D. Bovey, attd. Gord. Highrs., and to be transfd. to Gen. List. 15th June 1918.&quot;

<a href="http://www.london-gazette.co.uk/issues/31599/supplements/12721/" rel="nofollow">14 October 1919</a>, p. 12721: &quot;The undermentioned appts. are made:-- PERSONAL STAFF. A.D.C. -- Lt. D. P. Lithgow, 1st Dns, vice temp. Capt. Q. C. D. Bovey, Gen. List, from 30 May to 1st Aug 1919.&quot;

Full name Quentin Christopher Drummond Bovey:
<a href="http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/SearchUI/details/C1069039?descriptiontype=Full&amp;ref=WO+339/15111" rel="nofollow">discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/SearchUI/details/C10690...</a>

IWM Collections: <a href="http://www.iwm.org.uk/collections/item/object/205002903" rel="nofollow">www.iwm.org.uk/collections/item/object/205002903</a>

Possibly the same person on Cricket Archive, recorded as playing for Westminster School (Miscellaneous: 1913): <a href="http://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/1016/1016377/1016377.html" rel="nofollow">cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/1016/1016377/1016377.html</a>


Curiously, someone with the same name was apparently born Montreal in 1895, died 1987; see: <a href="http://wc.rootsweb.ancestry.com/cgi-bin/igm.cgi?op=GET&amp;db=breamefford&amp;id=I132450" rel="nofollow">wc.rootsweb.ancestry.com/cgi-bin/igm.cgi?op=GET&amp;db=br...</a>

In that connection, Lieutenant Q. C. D. Bovey ia mentioned as a member of the 5th Regiment (Royal Highlanders of
Canada) at the outbreak of war, headquartered in Montreal. See p. 26, in: <em>The call to arms: Montreal's Roll
of Honour, European War, 1914</em> (Montreal: Southam Press, 1914). See: <a href="https://archive.org/details/calltoarmsmontre00sanduoft" rel="nofollow">archive.org/details/calltoarmsmontre00sanduoft</a>

There are also a few mentions of a Mrs. Q. C. D. Bovey, I think mostly in a Canadian context.

According to the genealogy cited above, Quentin Bovey married a Elizabeth Maude Kennedy on the 15 September 1921, in Montreal. She had been born in Yarmouth, Nova Scotia on the 17 September 1898.
